The communication transport between project parts needs to be refactored.

We need to try to decouple/decompose this functionality as much as possible from the system's other business logic.

The client needs to request full information about the world state upon initialization, and then request/view a list of change snapshots from the last received to the current one (ideally, only the latest snapshot should be retrieved).

Each tick in the kernel, as it processes world events, accumulates world changes in the form of a change snapshot.

Use Redis as a snapshot storage; the client also gets change snapshots from there if it needs more than just the latest one.

Upon completion of the tick tasks, the change snapshot is saved to Redis.

If you have any clarifying questions, please ask them.


